sequenceDiagram
    actor User as Data Scientist
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard<br/>(Web UI)
    participant NBCtrl as notebook-controller
    participant Notebook as Workbench Pod<br/>(Jupyter/VSCode)
    participant MLflow as MLflow Server
    participant Feast as Feast<br/>Feature Store
    participant ModelReg as Model Registry
    participant KServe as KServe
    participant ModelCtrl as odh-model-controller
    participant Route as OpenShift Route
    participant TrustyAI as TrustyAI Service
    participant Client as External Client

    User->>Dashboard: 1. Access dashboard
    Dashboard->>NBCtrl: 2. Create Notebook CR
    NBCtrl->>Notebook: 3. Deploy workbench StatefulSet

    Note over Notebook,Feast: Model Development Phase
    Notebook->>Feast: 4a. Read features for training
    Notebook->>Notebook: 4b. Develop and train model
    Notebook->>MLflow: 4c. Log experiments and metrics

    Note over Notebook,ModelReg: Model Registration
    Notebook->>ModelReg: 5. Register trained model<br/>(version, metadata, artifacts)

    Note over User,KServe: Model Deployment
    User->>Dashboard: 6a. Create InferenceService
    Dashboard->>KServe: 6b. Create InferenceService CR
    KServe->>KServe: 6c. Deploy predictor pods<br/>(load model from S3/registry)

    Note over ModelCtrl,Route: OpenShift Integration
    ModelCtrl->>Route: 7. Create OpenShift Route<br/>(expose inference endpoint)

    Note over TrustyAI,KServe: AI Governance
    TrustyAI->>KServe: 8. Monitor inferences<br/>(fairness, drift detection)

    Note over Client,KServe: Inference
    Client->>Route: 9a. HTTPS inference request
    Route->>KServe: 9b. Forward to predictor
    KServe->>Client: 9c. Return predictions

    KServe-->>TrustyAI: 9d. Log inference for monitoring
    TrustyAI-->>MLflow: 9e. Log fairness metrics
